Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: Investigation of isotopic effects in nuclear reactions induced by 660-MeV protons.

x4freetext: Investigation of isotopic effects in nuclear reactions
induced by 660-MeV protons.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.19, p.16 (1974)

x4freetext: English transl.
.Telescope consisted from 3
surface-barrier silicon detectors-dE/dx detector,
thickness  23 and 40 mum, detector E ,thickness 800 mum
and anticoincidence detector, thickness 500 mum.

x4codes.hlp: Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna

x4freetext: Ionization chamber was calibrated by
monitor reactions.
Three independent series of measurements were obtained
with 58Ni and 64Ni , and three series with 1l2Sn and
124Sn. In order to detect possible systematic errors,
the measurements were repeated after long time
intervals and under different experimental conditions
(different targets positioned differently in the
chamber, different proton beam intensity, and
recalibration of the monitor).
The proton beam was monitored with an ionization
chamber that had been calibrated by means of the
reactions 27Al(p,3pn)24Na and 12C(p,pn)llC.
/by Authors/.Two isotopic effects are detected-
a correlation between the absolute production cross
sections for the product isotope particles and the
mass number of the target nuclear isotopes and a
variation of shape of the particle energy spectra when
substituting one target isotope for another.
Dependence of the ratio of the production cross
sections on the product particle isospin and on the
difference between their separation energies for two
target isotopes is found.
Last checking has been done.
DATE is corrected
SD: Updated to new date formats; BIB update;
corrected according to last EXFOR rules and Dict.
Ref. on English transl. (SNP,19,16,1974) added.
